sections.text: Terms, defined.For purposes of the Medicaid Access and Quality Act:(1) Nonhospital provider means a provider of physical health services that does not hold a license as a hospital under the Health Care Facility Licensure Act;(2) Physical health services means services billed under the medicaid practitioner fee schedule to meet the physical health needs of a patient; and(3) Rural means any county in Nebraska having a population of less than one hundred thousand residents.SourceLaws 2025, LB527, ยง 3.Effective Date: April 8, 2025Cross ReferencesHealth Care Facility Licensure Act, see section 71-401.
